President Trump addressed the United Nations General Assembly (UNGA) and highlighted the threats posed by rogue regimes. He emphasized the progress made in dealing with North Korea, Iran, and ISIS. The historic Singapore Summit with North Korean leader Kim Jong-Un resulted in a commitment to denuclearization. ISIS has lost most of its territory under the Trump Administration's changes in engagement rules. President Trump withdrew the United States from the Iran nuclear deal, emphasizing the need for a new agreement that addresses Iran's support for terrorism. The President called for strong, sovereign nations to work together to confront threats to civilization.